The paper deals with approximation algorithms for a graph partitioning problem, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The problem involves finding a cut of the vertex set so that the minimum, over the $k$ graphs, of the cut value is as large as possible. This problem is related to several areas of computer science, including algorithms, computational geometry, game theory, and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
